From: Blakestream-GaintB <sid@blakestream.local>
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] driver-baikalu: dynamic poll-master so disabling miner 0 doesn't break USB polling

Part 4 of the per-board ascdisable fix.

Architectural problem found while testing patches 1+2:

  baikal_scanhash() does the USB result polling for ALL miners on the
  device, but the poll is gated by `if (baikal->miner_id == 0)`. When
  ascdisable|0 is issued, sgminer's main loop suspends miner 0's thread
  (deven=DEV_DISABLED). That thread is the only one that calls
  baikal_process_result(), so USB result polling stops entirely. The
  other miners (1, 2) keep hashing but their results never get read off
  the STM32 bridge — no shares come back.

Symptom on the live device: ascdisable|0 → ASC 0 idles correctly,
but ASC 1 + 2 continue hashing at full rate with zero new Accepted
shares. Stats showed BKLU0 was the only board accumulating USB read
timeouts, confirming nothing else was driving the bus.

Fix: at the top of baikal_scanhash, scan info->miners[] and find the
LOWEST currently-enabled miner_id. That miner becomes the poll master
for this round. With miner 0 disabled, miner 1 takes over polling
naturally; with all 3 enabled, miner 0 polls (same as before).

Also collapse the broken cleanup-on-failure path inside scanhash:
the old code called baikal_cleanup() when baikal_process_result()
returned false, which is the same nuclear-option problem patch 2 fixed
in update_work. Replace with a warning + skip-this-cycle.
---
 driver-baikalu.c | 32 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 26 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/driver-baikalu.c b/driver-baikalu.c
--- a/driver-baikalu.c
+++ b/driver-baikalu.c
@@ -858,14 +858,34 @@ static int64_t baikal_scanhash(struct thr_info *thr)
     if (baikal->usbinfo.nodev) {
         return (-1);
     }

-    if (baikal->miner_id == 0) {
-        if (baikal_process_result(baikal) != true) {
-            baikal_cleanup(baikal);
-            return (-1);
-        }
-    }
-    else {
-        cgsleep_ms(50);
+    /* PATCH 4: Determine which miner_id should poll USB results.
+     * Originally hardcoded to 0, but if miner 0 is administratively
+     * disabled (ascdisable), sgminer suspends its thread, which would
+     * stop USB polling for everyone. Instead, the LOWEST currently-
+     * enabled miner_id polls. Also: do NOT cleanup the device on a
+     * transient process_result failure -- that nukes ALL miners. */
+    {
+        int _pm = 0, _i;
+        for (_i = 0; _i < info->miner_count; _i++) {
+            struct thr_info *_t = mining_thr[info->miners[_i].thr_id];
+            if (_t && _t->cgpu && _t->cgpu->deven != DEV_DISABLED) {
+                _pm = _i;
+                break;
+            }
+        }
+        if (baikal->miner_id == _pm) {
+            if (baikal_process_result(baikal) != true) {
+                applog(LOG_WARNING,
+                    "baikal_process_result transient failure miner %d, skipping (was: full cleanup)",
+                    baikal->miner_id);
+                return 0;
+            }
+        } else {
+            cgsleep_ms(50);
+        }
     }
